<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-31T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-31T08:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/316</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-31T14:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6318. Your telegram 4747, May [<hi rend="italic">April</hi>] 23, 4 p.m.,
                            last paragraph. British Government while equally reserving all such
                            rights as they may possess are most willing that there should be
                            reciprocal action between the two Governments and that United States
                            warships should remove enemy subjects or agents from British ships if
                            any such ships carrying persons of this description are encountered.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>